		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=11082">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Kohinoor" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Kohinoor">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Kohinoor" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=67&FN=Paladin&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1453488&TN=Group+Leaders&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1453488&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Been thinking about this just lately: what do you expect of your group leader?  I was thinking particularly of raid situations, and I was wondering from two viewpoints - the raid leader, and the group members.</P><P>To me as a raid leader, I like being around group leaders who know how to answer "Ready?".  To me, "yes" and "no" are the only viable alternatives.  "No, because..." is one better than just plain "no" as I can assess what's going on better.  Group leaders who don't answer drive me nuts.</P><P>To me as a group member, I like being around a group leader who gets buffs organised for the whole group.  If they do it for all when only one person asks, that's great ... but when they do it for everybody before they need to ask, that's real leadership.</P><P>Also group leaders who don't run away without making sure the whole group is with them is nice.</P><P>What do you guys think?</P><P><img src="http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/vikkibri/NDKohi.JPG" width=90 align=left><font face="Castellar,CenturySchoolbook,Arial" size="+1" color="CornflowerBlue"><b>Be strong<BR>Walk tall<BR>Go with pride</b></font><BR><a HREF="http://www.serenity-within.com/View_Member.php?Name=Kohinoor">Kohinoor Noblespirit of Felwithe</a><BR><a HREF="http://www.serenity-within.com">Serenity Within Guild</a></P><P>55th Crusade</P><P><a HREF="http://www.purenz.com/?98B94218-FEC9-430A-8CEF-AB2A52EAFCE1">New Zealand, home of Middle-Earth</a></font></P><P>Message edited by: Kohinoor (4/6/2002 5:49:39 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
