		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=67&FN=Paladin&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1453488&TN=Group+Leaders&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1455555&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Well, I found that the best way to run a raid is to be tough. The minute someone doubts your judgement, you're screwed. All you need is one person to say, hey this isn't right we need to do this.. for your authority to go away. If you're learning then well it's okay you have your teachers <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>I'm a bit harsh to an extent. I've had people get xloc'd out just for not paying attention and asking a the same common sense question twice. On certain raids, it can get the entire party killed. </P><P>If it's your first raid, okay I'll be nice. If you raided with me numerous times before, you know your role. I make it clear before it's even started. Call out MA/SA/TA. Name the shaman on Malo/Slow. Name the druid/ranger on snare. Name the wiz/druid/etc on annul. Same goes for buffs. No one should ask for buffs in a public channel. Name who's in charge of what buffs and have only tells be used. Once raid begins all fun talk is done in guild, now a chat channel. Puller calls in what's being pulled. Dispell/slow/snare etc duty is said, otherwise no one talks in the designated channel. With the new channels, raid leader, group leaders, and puller have their own channel to discuss situations.</P><P>my number one rule: NO ONE SENDS TELLS TO PULLER/RAID LEADER. all questions are to be directed to your designated group leader who in turn can ask the raid leader if they do not know the answer. </P><P>i'm pretty strict about organization. but at least my friends know that I mean well. I make raids fun, I want people to enjoy them.. but dying to stupidity or careless people is not fun and I prevent that at all costs. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20525>Shylah Soulshine</a><BR><i>Knight of Marr</i><BR><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/bsynchonline><i>Synch</a> ~ <a href=http